Variation . In a few specimens from Northern Brazil the mesepisternum and metepisternum are black dorsally. The axilla in some specimens is rounded apically. In some females the tuberculate process on the clypeus is flattened dorsoventrally (contrasting to the rounded process observed at the syntypes of
C . rostrata
).

Geographical Distribution . Argentina (Chaco), Bolivia (Santa Cruz), Brazil (Amapá, Mato Grosso, Mato Grosso do Sul, Pará, Paraíba, Santa Catarina, São Paulo), Paraguay (Concepción, Cordillera, Distrito Capital, San Pedro ), Peru (Cusco) (
Fig. 12
).
